---
import Header from "../../components/company/CompanyHeader.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/company/CompanyFooter.astro";

const LAST_UPDATED = "January 5, 2026";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Legal & Transparency | Strux</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy, Terms of Service, and Usage Limits for Strux iOS App Builder." />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#FDFBF7" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" />

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lato:wght@300;400;700&family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

    <style>
      /* --- GLOBAL VARIABLES (Ashak Studios Theme) --- */
      :root {
        --color-bg: #FDFBF7;
        --color-text-main: #2C2420;
        --color-text-muted: #6B635E;
        
        --color-primary: #8C6A5D;
        --color-primary-dark: #6D5248;
        
        --color-card-bg: #FFFFFF;
        --color-border: #E6DFD5;
        --shadow-sm: 0 1px 2px 0 rgba(44, 36, 32, 0.05);
      }

      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        background-color: var(--color-bg);
        color: var(--color-text-main);
        font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }

      h1, h2, h3, h4 {
        font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--color-text-main);
      }

      .container { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }

      /* --- HERO --- */
      .hero {
        padding: 100px 0 80px;
        text-align: center;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #E6DFD5;
        background: radial-gradient(circle at top, #F5F0E6 0%, #FDFBF7 70%);
      }
      
      .hero h1 {
        font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 56px);
        margin: 0 0 16px;
        color: #1A1410;
      }

      .meta-badge {
        display: inline-block; padding: 6px 16px;
        background: #EDE6D9;
        color: var(--color-primary-dark);
        font-size: 12px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
        font-weight: 700;
        border-radius: 4px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
      }

      /* TOC */
      .toc { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 32px; }
      .toc-btn {
        padding: 10px 24px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        background: #FFFFFF;
        border: 1px solid #D6CFC5;
        color: var(--color-text-muted);
        text-decoration: none;
        font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;
        font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 13px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.5px;
        transition: all 0.2s;
      }
      .toc-btn:hover {
        background: #FDFBF7;
        color: var(--color-primary);
        border-color: var(--color-primary);
      }

      /* --- LEGAL CARD --- */
      .legal-card {
        background: var(--color-card-bg);
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 60px;
        margin: 60px 0;
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
        scroll-margin-top: 40px;
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 32px;
        margin: 0 0 24px 0;
        padding-bottom: 24px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #F0EBE3;
      }
      
      h3 { font-size: 20px; color: #4A3F39; margin: 32px 0 12px; }
      p, li { font-size: 16px; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: 16px; }
      ul { margin: 0 0 24px 0; padding-left: 20px; }
      li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
      a { color: var(--color-primary); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--color-border); font-weight: 700; }
      a:hover { color: var(--color-primary-dark); border-bottom-style: solid; }

      /* Info Boxes */
      .box {
        padding: 24px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        margin: 32px 0;
        background: #F9F6F1; /* Çok açık bej */
        border-left: 3px solid var(--color-primary);
      }
      
      .box h4 { margin: 0 0 8px 0; font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; color: var(--color-primary); }
      .box p { margin: 0; font-size: 15px; color: #5D5550; }

      @media(max-width: 768px) {
        .legal-card { padding: 32px; margin: 40px 0; }
        .hero h1 { font-size: 32px; }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>

    <Header />

    <main>
      
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="container">
          <span class="meta-badge">Last Updated: {LAST_UPDATED}</span>
          <h1>Legal & Transparency</h1>
          <p style="color:#6B635E; max-width:600px; margin:0 auto;">
            Our commitment to secure, local-first development. <br>Understand your rights and responsibilities.
          </p>
          
          <div class="toc">
            <a class="toc-btn" href="#privacy">Data & Privacy</a>
            <a class="toc-btn" href="#fair-use">Usage Limits</a>
            <a class="toc-btn" href="#liability">Liability</a>
            <a class="toc-btn" href="#terms">Subscription</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="container">
        
        <article id="privacy" class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="section-title">Data Privacy & Storage</h2>
          
          <div class="box">
            <h4>Local-First Architecture</h4>
            <p>
              Strux is designed with security as a priority. The applications, code, and interfaces you create are <strong>stored locally on your device</strong>. We do not have access to your project files.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3>1. Project Data (On Device)</h3>
          <p>
            Every app you build, every line of JSON, and every UI layout remains in your device's sandbox storage. 
            Unlike web-based builders, your intellectual property never leaves your phone unless you explicitly choose to export or share it. 
            Currently, there are no community sharing features, ensuring your work remains 100% private.
          </p>

          <h3>2. Account Metadata (Secure Cloud)</h3>
          <p>
            We use a secure, encrypted cloud infrastructure solely to manage your subscription status and usage quotas. 
            We store the required datas: your anonymous User ID, name, email and your daily credit balance.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article id="fair-use" class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="section-title">Fair Usage & Limits</h2>
          <p>
            Strux utilizes advanced AI models to help you generate apps from text. To ensure the service remains fast and sustainable for everyone, we enforce specific usage tiers.
          </p>

          <h3>Free Tier Limits</h3>
          <p>
            Users on the Free Tier are provided with <strong>1 (one) AI generation right</strong> to test the capabilities of the system. 
            This allows you to experience the "Text-to-App" feature before committing to a subscription.
          </p>

          <h3>Pro Tier Limits</h3>
          <p>
            Subscribing to Strux Pro unlocks "Unlimited App Creation" in terms of project storage. However, for AI-assisted generation, a fair usage policy applies:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Daily Limit:</strong> Pro users are allocated <strong>5 (five) AI generation rights per day</strong>.</li>
            <li><strong>Reset:</strong> This quota resets automatically every 24 hours.</li>
            <li><strong>Manual Creation:</strong> You can always create and edit unlimited apps manually without using AI credits.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article id="liability" class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="section-title">User Liability & Responsibility</h2>
          
          <div class="box">
            <h4>Strux is a Tool, You are the Creator</h4>
            <p>
              Just like a hammer can build a house or break a window, Strux is a neutral development tool. You are solely responsible for what you build with it.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3>1. Content Responsibility</h3>
          <p>
            You agree that you are the sole creator of the applications built within Strux. 
            <strong>Ashak Studios accepts no liability</strong> for the function, content, or intent of the apps you create.
          </p>

          <h3>2. Prohibited Activities</h3>
          <p>
            You strictly agree <strong>NOT</strong> to use Strux to create:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Malicious applications (malware, spyware, viruses).</li>
            <li>Phishing tools or deceptive interfaces intended to steal user data.</li>
            <li>Apps that violate local laws or promote illegal activities.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Any user found creating malicious content will have their access revoked immediately without refund.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article id="terms" class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="section-title">Subscription & Terms</h2>
          
          <h3>1. Strux Pro Subscription</h3>
          <p>
            Strux Pro is offered as a monthly subscription service (e.g., $19.99/month) processed securely by Apple. 
            Upgrading removes all advertisements and unlocks the Pro features listed above.
          </p>

          <h3>2. Cancellation & Refunds</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Auto-Renewal:</strong> Your subscription automatically renews unless canceled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.</li>
            <li><strong>Cancellation:</strong> You can cancel anytime directly from your iPhone Settings (Apple ID > Subscriptions). You will retain access until the billing cycle ends.</li>
            <li><strong>Refunds:</strong> All payments are handled by Apple. We (the developers) do not have the ability to issue refunds directly. Please contact Apple Support for billing issues.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3. Contact Us</h3>
          <p>
            For support regarding the app functionality: <a href="mailto:contact@ashak.co">contact@ashak.co</a>
          </p>
        </article>

      </section>

    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>